## 1. Purpose
This policy protects [COMPANY]'s people, facilities, equipment, and the information (including PHI) they handle from physical and environmental threats — unauthorized access, theft, loss, and environmental hazards. It also documents how [COMPANY] inherits data-center physical security from [AWS] under the cloud shared-responsibility model.

## 2. Scope
This policy applies to all [COMPANY]-controlled workspaces ([offices, co-working spaces, and — where PHI is accessed — home offices]), all endpoints and removable media, and all workforce members. Physical security of the cloud infrastructure hosting [COMPANY]'s production systems and PHI is **inherited from [AWS]** and addressed in §6. [COMPANY] operates no production data centers of its own.

## 3. Policy
1. Access to [COMPANY] facilities and any areas where PHI may be viewed **shall** be restricted to authorized personnel and controlled by [badge/keycard/lock] systems.
2. Visitors **shall** be [signed in, escorted, and logged]; visitor access to areas where PHI is processed is restricted.
3. Workforce members **shall** observe a **clean desk** policy: PHI and confidential materials are not left unattended and are secured ([locked storage / shredding]) when not in use.
4. Workforce members **shall** observe a **clear screen** policy: devices auto-lock after [N — e.g. 10] minutes of inactivity and are locked when unattended.
5. Endpoints **shall** be encrypted at rest, enrolled in [MDM], and physically secured when traveling or working in public.
6. Disposal of media and printed PHI **shall** use secure destruction (shredding, cryptographic erasure) per `[media-disposal / data-classification]`.
7. Data-center physical and environmental controls **shall** be inherited from [AWS] and validated through AWS's third-party attestations (§6).

## 4. Facility & Office Security
- Entry to [COMPANY] offices is controlled by [keycard/badge]; access lists are reviewed [periodically] and revoked at offboarding per `hr-security-policy.md.template`.
- Server/network closets (if any) are [locked and access-restricted].
- Physical access events are [logged] where the system supports it.

## 5. Clean Desk, Clear Screen & Endpoint Protection
- No PHI or confidential information is left visible on desks, screens, whiteboards, or printers.
- Screens auto-lock and require re-authentication; privacy screens are used where PHI is viewed in shared/public spaces.
- Laptops and removable media are encrypted, kept under physical control, and never left unattended in public.
- Printing of PHI is minimized; printed PHI is collected immediately and shredded when no longer needed.

## 6. Cloud Data Centers — AWS Shared Responsibility (Inherited Control)
[COMPANY]'s production systems and PHI are hosted on **[AWS]**. Under the **AWS Shared Responsibility Model**, AWS is responsible for the **security *of* the cloud** — including the physical and environmental security of the data centers (perimeter security, access control, surveillance, power, cooling, fire suppression, and environmental monitoring). [COMPANY] **inherits** these physical and environmental controls and does **not** have or require physical access to AWS facilities.

[COMPANY] **shall**:
1. Rely on and retain [AWS]'s independent attestations (e.g., [SOC 2], [ISO 27001], [HITRUST inheritance / AWS Artifact reports]) as evidence of inherited data-center physical/environmental controls, and review them at least [annually] via `../vendor/third-party-risk-management-policy.md.template`.
2. Remain responsible for the **security *in* the cloud** — its data, configuration, access management, and the logical controls covered by the rest of the ISMS.
3. Document this inheritance in the Statement of Applicability so assessors can trace which physical controls are inherited vs. [COMPANY]-operated.

## 7. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer] | Owns this policy; validates AWS inherited controls; oversees clean desk/clear screen. |
| [Office Manager / Facilities] | Manages facility access, visitor logs, and physical safeguards. |
| [IT] | Enforces endpoint encryption, MDM, and auto-lock; manages secure disposal. |
| Managers | Reinforce clean desk/clear screen in their teams. |
| All Workforce | Follow clean desk/clear screen, protect endpoints and badges, and report physical security concerns. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 8. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 9. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Compliance is verified through facility access reviews, clean desk/clear screen walkthroughs, endpoint encryption/MDM reporting, and annual review of AWS attestations, reported to management review (`../governance/management-review.md.template`). Violations are handled per `hr-security-policy.md.template`, including the HIPAA workforce sanctions process (`../healthcare/sanctions-policy.md.template`).

